<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8005826>
    dc:description "Fig. 1. Morphology of Feabatrus gen. nov.A–C – head, dorsal (A), lateral (B), and ventral (C); D–F – prothorax, dorsal (D), lateral (E), and ventral (F); G – right elytron; H – apical half of elytron, lateral. Abbreviations: bef – basal elytral foveae, dc – discal carina, ds – discal stria, gc – gular carina, gf – gular fovea, hc – hypomeral carina, iblf – inner basolateral fovea, laf – lateral antebasal fovea, lls – lateral longitudinal sulcus, lpcf – lateral procoxal fovea, lpp – lateral postantennal pits, maf – median antebasal fovea, mbc – mediobasal carina, mls – median longitudinal sulcus, ms – marginal stria, oblf – outer basolateral fovea, omc – ocular-mandibular carina, vf – vertexal fovea. Scale bars: 0.2 mm in A–F; 0.25 mm in G, H." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8005826/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8005828>
    dc:description "Fig. 2. Morphology of Feabatrus gen. nov. A – meso- and metaventrite; B–D – abdomen, lateral (B), dorsal (C), and ventral (D). Abbreviations: blf – basolateral fovea, lmcf – lateral mesocoxal fovea, lmsf – lateral mesoventral fovea, lmtf – lateral metaventral fovea, mbf – mediobasal fovea, mmsf – median mesoventral fovea, s1–5 – sternites 1–5 (III–VII), t1–4 – tergites 1–4 (IV–VII). Scale bars: 0.5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8005828/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

